  description: "struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__('pack_into')==True / Struct.__dict__.__contains__('iter_unpack')==True / Struct.__dict__.__contains__('unpack_from')==True / Struct.__dict__.__len__()==16 — Struct.__dict__.__contains__('pack_into') is True ('pack_into' is a key in Struct.__dict__; struct.Struct.pack_into(buffer, offset, *values) writes packed bytes into a writable buffer at the given offset; struct_extra160 anchors this membership; 'pack_into'(9 chars) is the Struct instance method corresponding to the module-level struct.pack_into function); Struct.__dict__.__contains__('iter_unpack') is True ('iter_unpack' is a key in Struct.__dict__; Struct.iter_unpack(buffer) returns an iterator of tuples unpacked from successive items in buffer; added in Python 3.4; struct_extra160 anchors; 'iter_unpack'(11 chars) tied with 'unpack_from'(11) as longest method name in Struct.__dict__); Struct.__dict__.__contains__('unpack_from') is True ('unpack_from' is a key in Struct.__dict__; Struct.unpack_from(buffer, offset=0) unpacks from buffer at offset; struct_extra160 anchors; 'unpack_from'(11 chars)); Struct.__dict__.__len__() is 16 (confirmed; 16 keys total; 9 dunder + 7 non-dunder; first structdict163 anchor for pack_into/iter_unpack/unpack_from __contains__ as a combined table)"
  kind: python_call_eq
